<paragraph blockId="9.[151,558,1368,1394]" box="[151,558,1368,1394]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,558,1368,1394]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,558,1368,1394]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirkaldy" authorityName="Kirkaldy" box="[238,558,1368,1394]" class="Insecta" family="Macroveliidae" genus="Rheumatogonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,437,1368,1394]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Rheumatogonus</emphasis>
Kirkaldy
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1438,1716]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[286,467,1439,1463]" class="Insecta" family="Macroveliidae" genus="Rheumatogonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[286,467,1439,1463]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Rheumatogonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Southeast Asia was revised by Chen &amp; Nieser (
<number box="[1093,1152,1439,1463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="2002.0">2002</number>
) and nine species were recognized. Similar to other members of 
<taxonomicName box="[634,777,1475,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ptilomerinae">Ptilomerinae</taxonomicName>
, males and females can be identified based on genitalic structure and non-genitalic characters, respectively (Chen &amp; Nieser 
<number box="[970,1031,1511,1535]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="2002.0">2002</number>
). However, accurate identification requires male specimens. This genus is distributed in the tropical forests of the Oriental Region and prefers slow reaches of montane streams in forested areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen" box="[710,891,1583,1608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" refString="Andersen, N. M. (1982) The semiaquatic bugs (Hemiptera, Gerromorpha). Phylogeny, adaptations, biogeography and classification. Entomonograph. Vol. 3. Scandinavian Science Press Ltd., Klampenborg, Denmark, 546 pp." type="book" year="1982">
Andersen 
<number box="[832,891,1583,1607]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[908,1153,1583,1608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" refString="Chen, P. - P. &amp; Zettel, H. (1998) Key to genera and subgenera of Gerridae (Gerromorpha) of Thailand and adjacent countries, with a check-list of species known from Thailand. Amemboa, 2, 24 - 41." type="journal article" year="1998">
Chen &amp; Zettel 
<number box="[1094,1153,1583,1607]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, Chen &amp; Nieser 
<number box="[1364,1425,1583,1607]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="2002.0">2002</number>
). Members of this genus in 
<collectingCountry box="[445,545,1619,1644]" name="Thailand" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Thailand</collectingCountry>
are yellowish green in color when they are alive, but become yellowish brown in alcohol or exposure to light. Two species have been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[966,1066,1655,1680]" name="Thailand" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(Chen &amp; Nieser 
<number box="[1270,1330,1655,1679]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="2002.0">2002</number>
), both of which were collected in the 
<taxonomicName box="[466,596,1691,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tennaserim">Tennaserim</taxonomicName>
Mountain Range.
</paragraph>
